Peter Irons' article is only one part of the Montana Law Reviews take on this.  The other side was submitted by David DeWolf, Casey Luskin and John West and can be read here:     http://www.discovery.org/a/2125    .If you want a thorough analysis of the Dover v. Kitzmiller ruling you should read "Traipsing Into Evolution" -- www.traipsingintoevolution.  Like modern evolutionary theory there is more than just one side to the debate. 